IaaSs provide the ability for customers to "tag" VMs, databases and other resources with custom labels and metadata values. 
Apply one or more tags to your clusters to simplify organizing, managing, searching for, and filtering resources within your IaaS-provided management console and other tools.  

<% if current_page.data.pkscommand == "create" %>
If your <%= vars.product_short %> deployment is on:

* **AWS**: You must tag your subnets with your new cluster's unique identifier before adding the subnets to the 
<%= vars.product_short %> workload load balancer. 
After you complete the [Create a Kubernetes Cluster](#create) procedure above, 
follow the instructions in [AWS Prerequisites](./deploy-workloads.html#aws) in _Deploying and Exposing Basic Linux Workloads_.
* **Azure**: You can use the PKS CLI to tag your clusters by following the steps in 
[Tag Your Clusters Using the PKS CLI](#tagging-cli), below.  
* **GCP**, **vSphere** or **vSphere with NSX-T**: You can tag your clusters using your IaaS-provided management console.  
